  "content": {
    "prompt": "An inverted right triangle star pattern of N rows contains N-i+1 asterisks in the i-th row. Construct a program that receives the number of rows in the inverted right triangle star pattern and prints that triangle. For example, when the number of rows in the inverted right triangle star pattern is 5, the program prints the following output:\\n*****\\n****\\n***\\n**\\n*",
    "source_code": "#Step 1: Read the number of rows in the inverted right triangle star pattern\nN = int(input(\"Enter the number of rows in the inverted right triangle star pattern:\"))\n#Step 2: Print the rows in the star pattern, one by one\nfor i in range(1, N+1):  \n    #Step 2.1: Generate the asterisks in the i-th row \n    row = \"\"\n    for j in range(1, N-i+2):  \n        row = row + \"*\"\n    #Step 2.2: Print the asterisks in the i-th row\n    print(row)"
  },
